<font color="#FF0000">DRIFTING THOUGHTS OF A FNG</font><br>
<tt>Sun Feb 15 19:17:18 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
&quot;Judge No One&quot; ... a very admirable quest. Yet, I find that an almost impossible feat as it seems, we judge ourselves day by day. Looking in the mirror ... wondering, am I congruent with my moral philosophy, do I believe in that which I follow, am I following my heart, and a million other questions that play over. I guess I feel more comfortable with acceptance ... and maybe ... once I begin to accept myself as I am, for who I am, and what I believe, I can better accept the differences in those around me ... for who am I to think that my views are &quot;right&quot; or &quot;better&quot;? I only have my own life experience to measure that with ... much different than the life experience of those around me ... thus, I am limited in that regard.<br><br>
As for the possiblity of another conflict, I truly hope that it does not happen, yet I feel very insignificant in that I have no manner in which to truly influence the decision making process. Somehow, I have a hard time fully believing the information given out to the population. <br><br>
There is one thing that I am sure of though. If conflict does ensue, I will support the men and women who are there to serve. The thing that keeps it in perspective for me is .... &quot;to serve&quot; .... they are there to serve their country in a manner that best fits them. And in my heart I believe that those that are there to truly serve seek no medals, no glory ... but simply, respect for putting forth their heart and soul for something they believe in ... serving their country. 
